== Vegetables Preparation ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1%unit} into strips.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} and @cooking oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Sausage and Sauce ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{18%ounce}, onion, and bell pepper; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage is browned and cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes} (for 8 servings, cook sausage and veggies in batches). Transfer to a #large bowl{}.

Add @marinara cup{14%ounce}, @garlic powder{2%tsp}, and @chicken stock concentrate{2} to bowl with sausage mixture. Stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Add @tortelloni{18%ounce} and @water{1/3%cup} to bowl with sausage mixture and sauce; stir to combine.

Transfer tortelloni and sausage mixture to a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} (two 9-by-13-inch baking dishes for 8 servings). Dollop with ricotta and sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake on top rack (top and middle racks for 8) until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Remove from oven and let rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Serve tortelloni bake family style directly from the #baking dish{} or divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.